---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Tank Squad Building" 
  description="Tank squad hero focus order, skill priorities, and mid-game build guide for Last War: Survival."
>
  <h1>Tank Squad Building</h1>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p>Tank is the most popular and forgiving choice for mid-game players. Many strong players run two full Tank squads before diversifying.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Hero Focus Order (Recommended)</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Get these heroes to 5 stars in roughly this order before heavily investing the next one. This is the fastest path to a dominant main squad.</p>

  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Priority</th>
          <th>Hero</th>
          <th>Why This Order</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold text-[#f59e0b]">1</td>
          <td><strong>Kimberly (Kim)</strong></td>
          <td>Your primary DPS and biggest power spike. Push her to 5★ as fast as possible.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">2</td>
          <td><strong>Stetmann</strong></td>
          <td>Excellent all-rounder with strong skills. Next highest priority after Kim.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">3</td>
          <td><strong>Williams</strong></td>
          <td>Best main frontline tank for most players. High durability.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">4</td>
          <td><strong>Murphy</strong></td>
          <td>Great support tank, especially strong vs Missile comps.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">5</td>
          <td><strong>Marshall</strong></td>
          <td>Solid backline support / secondary DPS. Good flex option.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Positioning (Tank Squad)</h2>
  <p>Standard strong formation for most Tank squads:</p>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Front Left:</strong> Williams (main tank, draws the most fire)</li>
    <li><strong>Front Right:</strong> Murphy (support tank)</li>
    <li><strong>Back Left:</strong> Kim (highest priority DPS — focus fire here)</li>
    <li><strong>Back Center:</strong> Stetmann (strong secondary DPS — often the safest spot as it is targeted last)</li>
    <li><strong>Back Right:</strong> Marshall (support / flex)</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-xs text-[#5e6b85] mt-2">Note: Back row center is frequently the last place the opponent targets. This makes it an excellent home for one of your key damage dealers.</p>

  <h2>Skill Priority</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">Max skills in this rough order on your core heroes:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 text-sm">
    <li>Active / top-row damage or key buff skills on Kim first</li>
    <li>Stetmann’s key skills</li>
    <li>Williams’ tanking / taunt skills</li>
    <li>Passives and lower priority skills last</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Visual Guides (Highly Recommended)</h2>
  <p>Community-made visual squad references — check the subreddit's guide threads — often show:</p>
  <ul class="text-sm">
    <li>Exact hero focus order with headshots</li>
    <li>Skill priority in 3 clear levels</li>
    <li>Star and level prioritization</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Once Kim and Stetmann are both at 5★ with decent gear, your Tank squad will feel dramatically stronger. Stay focused — spreading resources is the fastest way to stay weak.</p>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <a href="/squad-building" class="text-[#f59e0b]">← Back to Squad Building Principles</a>
  </div>
</Layout>